user.name: Dex Ezekiel
user.bio: Photographer living in Anaheim. Working with businesses and brands.

results.description: Notwithstanding the wonderful textures and patterns in the rocks, the lower Antelope Canyon exhibits the rare opportunity to catch the different color temperatures of light, going from the cold purple at the bottom to the bright white at the top

One of the most beautiful things I’ve seen in the desert is Antelope Canyons. With its wavy walls, smooth texture and beautiful curves, I began to see the abstract beauty that nature has taken thousands of years to create. Mostly known for their light beams and beautiful colors, I decided to take a monochrome, abstract approach that is rarely seen. This is part 1 of a 10 picture series.
